data.title: Dierks, Arkansas with a population of 900 wins T-Mobile’s Friday Night 5G Lights competition with nearly 2M votes.
data.description: In Bellevue, Washington, T-Mobile has announced the winner of the Friday Night 5G Lights competition. After over 8 million votes were cast across the nation for the Top 25 finalists, Dierks High School in Arkansas emerged victorious. As the champion, they will receive a $1 million field upgrade. Despite being a small community of 900 people, Dierks High School showcased the spirit of small-town America by uniting and mobilizing support globally for their cause.

data.title: Propel Software names Zack Jha as Chief Revenue Officer (CRO) to lead growth efforts, with over 3 decades of experience.
data.description: Propel Software, a California-based company, has announced Zack Jha as their Chief Revenue Officer (CRO). Jha, with over 30 years of leadership experience at companies like Oracle, PTC, and AWS, will lead the teams driving the company's growth. Propel Software is known for its innovative product value management platform that revolutionizes how businesses handle product creation, marketing, sales, and service. Jha's appointment signifies the company's commitment to expanding, with a focus on leveraging his expertise to further propel the company forward.

data.title: Beeline sets record with 21 locked loans worth nearly $8 million on the day Fed cut rates by 25 basis points.
data.description: On October 29, 2025, Beeline (NASDAQ: BLNE), a digital mortgage lender catering to next-gen homeowners, sealed 21 loans totaling nearly $8 million in locked volume, coinciding with the Fed's second consecutive month of rate cuts. This milestone set new highs for Beeline's leading indicators, with locked loans and volume serving as robust predictors of revenue over the upcoming 30 to 45 days.

data.title: Wealth.com partners with Advyzon for estate planning, serving 2,400 advisors nationwide, streamlining workflows.
data.description: Phoenix - Wealth.com, a prominent estate planning platform for financial advisors, has revealed a fresh integration with Advyzon, a comprehensive wealth management platform favored by over 2,400 financial advisors across the nation. This partnership aims to streamline the process of integrating estate planning into the daily operations of advisors utilizing Advyzon. Through this integration, client and portfolio information seamlessly transfers from Advyzon to Wealth.com, allowing advisors to efficiently manage estate planning within their workflows.

data.title: 3D Systems to release Q3 2025 financial results on Nov 4, 2025, with conference call on Nov 5 at 8:30 am ET.
data.description: 3D Systems, traded as DDD on NYSE, disclosed its plan to unveil the financial outcomes for the third quarter of 2025, concluding on September 30, 2025, post market closure on Tuesday, November 4, 2025. A conference call and webcast are slated to delve into these figures on Wednesday, November 5, 2025, at 8:30 a.m. Eastern Time.

data.title: Takeda's weak Q2 means lowered 2025 outlook, with $1.31 billion net profit, $7.52 billion sales, and EPADS of 43 cents.
data.description: Takeda Pharmaceutical Company Limited (NYSE: TAK) recorded an adjusted net profit of 201.6 billion Japanese yen (around $1.31 billion) for the second quarter of 2025. Earnings per American Depositary Share (EPADS) stood at 43 cents, which was slightly lower than the anticipated 44 cents. However, EPS in yen dropped by 4.5% to 128 yen. Total sales for the quarter reached $7.52 billion (1.18 trillion yen), falling short of the estimated $8.08 billion. The company's first-half results for fiscal year 2025 were in line with the anticipated progress in its core operations. Takeda recently engaged Nabla Bio's Generative AI Platform for Antibody Design in a significant $1 billion agreement.

data.title: Advance Auto Parts reported Q3 earnings of 92 cents/share, up from a loss of 5 cents last year, with revenue at $2.04B.
data.description: Advance Auto Parts Inc. saw a surge in its stock price on Thursday following the release of its third-quarter financial results. The company reported adjusted earnings of 92 cents per share, marking a significant improvement from a loss of 5 cents per share in the same period last year and surpassing analysts' expectation of 75 cents per share for the quarter. Quarterly revenue stood at $2.04 billion, slightly above the consensus estimate of $2.03 billion but down 5.2% from the previous year's $2.15 billion. Comparable store sales for the third quarter experienced a notable 3% increase.Furthermore, the adjusted gross profit margin for the quarter witnessed an enhancement to 44.8% from 42.3% year-over-year, while the adjusted operating income margin climbed to 4.4% from 0.7%. The company's turnaround plan appears to be making progress despite modest guidance, as mentioned by analysts. The third quarter ended on a positive note for Advanced Auto Parts as it showed promising growth in various key financial indicators. For further details, the complete story can be accessed on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Upwind introduces Exposure Validation Engine for Cloud Security, offering real-time validation for live cloud exposures.
data.description: In San Francisco, Upwind unveiled its Exposure Validation Engine, a groundbreaking feature in Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM). This unique capability provides real-time validation within the cloud security layer, allowing teams to confirm cloud exposures accurately in practical settings. The introduction aligns with Upwind's inclusion in the 2026 Fortune × Lightspee list, showcasing its innovation in the industry.

data.title: Treaty Oak Clean Energy and Meta signed long-term power purchase agreements for 2 Louisiana solar projects to drive clean energy transition.
data.description: In Austin, Texas, a recent partnership is making waves in the realm of clean energy in Louisiana. The collaboration between Meta is fueling the state's transition towards clean energy. Additionally, Treaty Oak is broadening its reach in the renewable energy sector on a national scale. This initiative is set to have a significant impact on the state's energy landscape, bringing about substantial changes in the way energy is sourced and utilized.

data.title: Animal Crossing: New Horizons gets Nintendo Switch 2 Edition with enhanced features like higher resolution visuals and online play for up to 12 players.
data.description: Residents of Redmond, Wash., can expect exciting updates coming to their island getaway with the launch of the Animal Crossing: New Horizons – Nintendo Switch 2 Edition. This enhanced game for the Nintendo Switch 2 system offers improved features such as higher resolution visuals, mouse controls, and the use of the system's microphone for an in-game megaphone. Online play is now available for up to 12 players, along with the addition of CameraPlay. Don't miss out on the enhanced experience with the latest edition of this popular game.

data.title: Ben's Soft Pretzels partners with Square for growth at 185+ locations, enhancing operations and customer engagement.
data.description: In Elkhart, Indiana, Ben's Soft Pretzels, the rapidly expanding premium pretzel franchise in the United States, has joined forces with Square to streamline its operations across the country. Utilizing Square's comprehensive restaurant platform, Ben's has revolutionized its customer interactions and operational processes. This partnership has enabled the franchise to enhance loyalty programs, as well as gain valuable back-of-house data insights. Since its establishment in 2008, Ben's has been able to maintain the original authentic pretzel experience that traces back to its Amish homestead roots.

data.title: Prospero.ai's equity crowdfunding on Republic nears end with over $470k from 450+ investors, fueling product development.
data.description: Prospero.ai, a distinguished AI-driven investing platform aiding retail investors in trading like experts, shared today that it is in the last day of its equity crowdfunding campaign on Republic. The campaign has garnered over 470k from 450+ investors thus far. This marks the final chance for new investors to participate before the round concludes. The capital raised will expedite the development of Prospero.ai’s product ecosystem, inclusive of the debut of its latest offerings.

data.title: L3Harris Technologies (NYSE: LHX) reports Q3 revenue of $5.66B, better than expected, with EPS of $2.70. Total revenue up 7% YoY. Positive outlook for 2025.
data.description: L3Harris Technologies Inc (NYSE: LHX) released its third-quarter financial results before the market opened on Thursday, demonstrating strong bullish momentum. The company reported total revenue of $5.66 billion for the quarter, surpassing analyst predictions of $5.52 billion. Adjusted earnings for Q3 were $2.70 per share, exceeding the estimated $2.58 per share. In comparison to the previous year, total revenue saw a 7% increase. For further details, the complete article can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Comcast beats Q3 estimates with revenue of $31.2 billion, gains 414,000 wireless line customers but loses 104,000 broadband customers. Verizon gains 306,000 broadband customers.
data.description: Comcast Corp (CMCSA) saw an increase in stock value following the release of their third-quarter financial results, which surpassed expectations. The company's revenue stood at $31.2 billion, surpassing the estimated $30.7 billion. They reported a total of 414,000 new domestic wireless line additions. Despite this success, Comcast did experience a loss of 104,000 broadband customers during the quarter. In comparison, Verizon Communications Inc (VZ) gained 306,000 broadband customers. Additionally, T-Mobile US, Inc (TMUS) acquired 560,000 broadband net customer additions, indicating strong growth in this sector. These figures reflect the competitive landscape in the telecommunications industry.
